{"_response_info":{"status":"ok"},"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/creditor-bankruptcy-petitions.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/creditor-bankruptcy-petitions","title":"Creditor bankruptcy petitions","format":"answer","updated_at":"2012-12-12T10:58:35+00:00","details":{"need_id":"2084","business_proposition":false,"description":"Making someone bankrupt is one way to recover money owed to you – bankruptcy petition fees and download a guide to creditor bankruptcy petitions","language":"en","body":"\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>Making someone bankrupt is one way to recover money owed to you - you will have to pay a fee.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>A <a href=\"http://www.civilmediation.justice.gov.uk/\" title=\"Find a mediation service\" rel=\"external\">mediation service</a> could be quicker and cheaper than making someone bankrupt. Mediation is when an impartial person helps two sides work out an agreement.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Fees</h2>\n<p>The court fees to make someone bankrupt are: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>£700 petition deposit (for managing the bankruptcy) </li>\n  <li>£220 for court costs</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You can pay the fees using cash, postal orders or a cheque made payable to Her Majesty’s Courts &amp; Tribunal Service. </p>\n\n<h2>The basics</h2>\n<p>You’ll need a solicitor or debt specialist to help you because you&rsquo;ll have to: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>petition (apply to) the court to issue a bankruptcy order </li>\n  <li>prove the debtor owes £750 or more (to 1 or more creditors) </li>\n  <li>prove the debtor can’t repay what they owe</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.bis.gov.uk/assets/bispartners/insolvency/docs/publication-word/howtomake.doc\" title=\"Download 'Dealing with debt, how to make someone bankrupt' (DOC, 200KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Dealing with debt, how to make someone bankrupt’ (DOC, 200KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>There is a different process for <a href=\"http://www.aib.gov.uk/services/creditor-petition\" title=\"Creditor petitions - Scotland\" rel=\"external\">creditor bankruptcy petitions in Scotland.</a></p>\n</div>\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Funding and debt","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/business%2Ffunding-debt.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes bankruptcy, business finance and recovering debt","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=business%2Ffunding-debt","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/business/funding-debt"},"parent":{"title":"Businesses and self-employed","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/business.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Information about starting up and running a business in the UK, including help if you're self employed or a sole trader.","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=business","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/business"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Court claims, debt and bankruptcy","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/tax%2Fcourt-claims-debt-bankruptcy.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes recovering debts, registering for bankruptcy and as a creditor","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=tax%2Fcourt-claims-debt-bankruptcy","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/tax/court-claims-debt-bankruptcy"},"parent":{"title":"Money and tax","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/tax.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes VAT, debt and inheritance tax","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=tax","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/tax"},"parent":null}}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/make-court-claim-for-money.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/make-court-claim-for-money","title":"Ma